The paper discusses the use of spin torque memory (ST-MRAM) for implementing synaptic weights in hardware neural networks, which falls under the category of emerging technologies (cs.ET). The paper also focuses on energy savings, which is a common concern in the field of neural networks (cs.NE). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of approximate storage approaches, which is a topic in the field of approximate computing (cs.AR). The paper also addresses the issue of device variability, which is a concern in the field of control systems (cs.SY). Finally, the paper discusses the use of magnetoresistive random access memory (MRAM), which is a topic in the field of electromagnetics (cs.EM).
